  "prompt": "Is watching porn illegal in US?",
  "response": "In the United States, **adult pornography is generally legal** when it involves consenting adults and adheres to specific federal and state regulations. However, there are important legal boundaries and restrictions to be aware of:\n\n### **Legal Forms of Pornography:**\n- **Consenting Adults:** Pornographic content produced and distributed with the full consent of all involved adults is legal. This includes a wide range of adult entertainment available through various media platforms.\n- **Protected Speech:** The U.S. Supreme Court has recognized certain forms of adult pornography as protected under the First Amendment, which guarantees freedom of speech.\n\n### **Illegal Forms of Pornography:**\n- **Child Pornography:** Any depiction of minors (individuals under 18) in sexual activities is strictly illegal and subject to severe federal and state penalties.\n- **Non-Consensual Content:** Content that involves sexual activities without consent, including certain types of revenge porn or content featuring coercion, is illegal.\n- **Obscene Material:** While not all explicit content is illegal, material that meets the legal definition of \"obscene\" is not protected by the First Amendment. The determination of obscenity typically follows the **Miller Test**, established by the Supreme Court, which considers whether:\n  1. **Whether the average person, applying contemporary community standards, would find that the work, taken as a whole, appeals to the prurient interest.**\n  2. **Whether the work depicts or describes, in a patently offensive way, sexual conduct specifically defined by applicable state law.**\n  3. **Whether the work, taken as a whole, lacks serious literary, artistic, political, or scientific value.**\n  \n  If a work meets all three criteria, it can be deemed obscene and thus illegal.\n\n### **Regulations and Restrictions:**\n- **Age Verification:** Websites distributing adult content are required to verify that viewers are of legal age (18 years or older).\n- **Record-Keeping:** Producers of pornographic content must maintain records proving the ages and consent of all performers (commonly known as \"2257 Records\" after Section 2257 of the U.S. Code).\n- **Distribution Limits:** Certain types of content may be restricted in distribution, especially across state lines or international borders, depending on varying state laws and international agreements.\n\n### **State Laws:**\nWhile federal laws provide a general framework, individual states may have additional regulations or restrictions regarding the production, distribution, and consumption of pornography. It's essential to be aware of and comply with the laws specific to your state or locality.\n\n### **Employment and Public Settings:**\nEven though adult pornography is legal, its consumption may be restricted or prohibited in certain settings, such as workplaces, schools, or public areas, based on institutional policies or community standards.\n\n### **Seeking Legal Advice:**\nLaws surrounding pornography can be complex and subject to change. If you have specific concerns or questions about the legality of certain content or activities, it's advisable to consult with a qualified attorney who specializes in media or criminal law.\n\n### **Conclusion:**\nWhile watching legal adult pornography is not illegal in the U.S., it is subject to a framework of laws and regulations designed to protect individuals and uphold community standards. Ensuring that all content consumed is legal and consensual is crucial to avoiding legal repercussions.",
